Build Gate Proviso:
- Never render or expose spreadsheet letter identifiers in generated content or public-facing pages.
- Always use semantic entity names (for example, `Intervention Dominance`, `Coverage Timing`, `Evidence Type`).
- Treat any letter-identifier wording in generated outputs as a validation failure that must be fixed before build.

## BRS hub Dietary Guidance (reader-facing)

Canonical authoring contract: **`system/brs-hub-levers-schema.md`** (BRS Dietary Guidance Standard). **Reference hub:** BRS2 (`methylation-one-carbon-metabolism.md`).

- Hub Dietary Guidance must contain **practical dietary advice only**.
- Do **not** publish authoring instructions, deduplication notes, or schema commentary in the hub panel (e.g. “present once”, “do not repeat”, “not already captured by KC…”).
- Deduplication is enforced in the schema; the page shows Pattern → Nutrients → Biology → Target Foods (+ KC/PM labels).
- **KC-integrated layout (canonical):** no standalone hub Key Constraints section. Inside Dietary Guidance: flow line → **Key Constraints of BRS{n}** → per-KC substrate rows → **Additional Mechanism-Specific Dietary Levers**.
- Two short intro paragraphs under **Dietary and Lifestyle Levers**: (1) **Biology** — shared pool / Key Constraint requirement; (2) **Daily regulation** — what meal quality, timing and recovery determine. Reference: BRS4.

- Each biological target page must be tagged with the Therapeutic Areas it is involved in.
- Each biological target page must be tagged with "Biological Target" so that it appears in index.md.
- Each biological target page must be tagged with the name of the biological target (e.g. Hormonal Response) so we can refer to it from a substance.
- In the front matter, list_image must be: /img/icons/biological-targets.svg

Page structure:

- Overview: A single paragraph description describing the scope of the biological target.
- Therapeutic Areas: Must use the <TagList tag="biological target" filter="therapeutic-areas" /> here.
- Substances: Must use the <TagList tag="biological target" filter="substances" /> here.
- Biological Mechanisms and Implications: From paper.txt talk about any problems arising from issues with this biological area. e.g. "Protein forward meals (25-35g of protein) for focus and alertness."
- References: A list of findings or scientific principles per **`system/brs-citation-reference-standard.md`**: inline `[Author et al., Year]` in body; References entries as `[Author et al. (Year) — Short Descriptive Study Topic](/docs/papers/BRAIN-Diet-References#<ref>)`. Use `paper.txt` and bibliography where applicable.
- Modulators must not be added without evidence. If a modulator is introduced, cite inline per **`system/brs-citation-reference-standard.md`** and add a matching References entry.
- Ensure cited bibliography entries include DOI or source URL so the bibliography provides a clickable path to the original source.

An example for the References section might look like this:

- [Prehn-Kristensen et al. (2018) — Reduced Gut Microbial Diversity in ADHD](/docs/papers/BRAIN-Diet-References#prehn-kristensen_reduced_2018)

Use the `methylation.md` page as an example.
